                            <comment id="15230031" author="asamir" created="Thu, 7 Apr 2016 10:03:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ndimiduk&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ndimiduk&quot;&gt;Nick Dimiduk&lt;/a&gt; i have notice same behavior on master branch. After some digging i have found that connection to zookeeper is created by &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
CompactionState compactionState = admin.getCompactionState(table.getName());
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt; 
&lt;p&gt; in table.jsp. &lt;br/&gt;
We are always creating zookeeper connection in  admin#getCompactionState() in order to check compaction state of &apos;hbase:meta&apos; table. We can change this to create zk connection only in case when we are checking &apos;hbase:meta table&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will create new ticket to add this change to admin#getCompactionState() for master branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15230696" author="ndimiduk" created="Thu, 7 Apr 2016 17:50:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Very well. Closing as superceded by of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-15606&quot; title=&quot;Limit creating zk connection in HBaseAdmin#getCompactionState() only to case when &amp;#39;hbase:meta&amp;#39; is checked.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-15606&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-15606&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
